Here’s the concise extraction of material information from the ASX announcement:

Exploration Update – Key Highlights

  • New ultramafic-gabbroic intrusion intersected at MS1 (6km SE of Oval Cu-Ni discovery), with weak sulphide mineralisation (0.3% Cpy, 0.2% Po, 0.2% Py over 86.2m).
  • Downhole EM at MS1 identified a conductive plate (6m x 6m, 8000 siemens), suggesting potential for deeper/lateral mineralisation.
  • MS2 drilling intersected gabbroic rock, structurally linked to Oval but no mineralisation yet – deeper targets to be refined via mag surveys.
  • SAMSON EM surveys commenced at Oval and will expand to MS1.

Pending Catalysts

  • Assay results from Phase 3 drilling expected late June 2025.
  • First metallurgical test results from Oval anticipated July/August 2025.

Next Steps

  • Ongoing EM surveys at Oval and MS1.
  • Magnetic surveys planned for MS2 to refine targets.

Material Impact

Expands prospective footprint beyond Oval, reinforcing district-scale potential. Visual estimates await lab confirmation.

No capital raising, financials, or operational disruptions identified.

Material Information Summary - Exploration Results (Kpali Gold Prospect, Ghana)

  • High-grade gold intercepts confirmed at Kpali prospect:
  • 1m at 20.66g/t Au from 41m (25KPRC018).
  • 19m at 2.93g/t Au from 77m (including higher-grade sub-intervals).

  • Multiple additional intercepts >2g/t Au, demonstrating continuity over 650m strike and 120m depth.

  • Upcoming catalysts:

  • Bundi prospect assays (5 holes) expected early-July 2025.
  • Kandia Project assays (10 holes) due mid-July 2025.

  • Follow-up RC drilling at Kpali/Kandia planned for September 2025 (subject to weather/rig availability).

  • Exploration strategy:

  • Auger drilling to commence July 2025 to test new targets.

  • High-resolution aeromagnetic data and structural reinterpretation underway to guide future drilling.

  • Regional context: Located in Ghana’s emerging gold belt, proximal to 5.1Moz Namdini and 2.8Moz Black Volta deposits.

No capital raising, financial数据, or material changes to capital structure identified.

Summary of ASX Announcement (CHW) – 16 June 2025

Material Information for Capital Markets/Trading Decisions:

  • Exploration Results:
  • High-grade Total Heavy Mineral (THM) intercepts at Mpyupyu Dune deposit include:
    • 2.92m @ 27.98% THM (incl. 0.61m @ 40.43% THM).
    • 4.48m @ 14.45% THM (incl. 1.96m @ 21.06% THM).
    • 1.94m @ 18.38% THM and 2.78m @ 24.75% THM.
  • Confirms higher-grade mineralisation in two sub-parallel lobate strandlines.

  • Existing Inferred Resource: 19.9Mt @ 4.2% THM (Dune portion: 3.5Mt @ 7.1% THM).

  • Near-Term Catalysts:

  • Mposa deposit Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE) expected in "coming weeks".
  • Scoping Study (handled by TZMI) targeting HMS deposits, results expected Q3 2025.

  • Rare Earth Element (REE) assay results from carbonatite drilling anticipated "in coming weeks".

  • Operational Efficiency:

  • Faster assay turnaround at Light Deep Earth (LDE) lab accelerating MRE timelines.

  • No capital raising, trading halt, or liquidity events disclosed.

Conclusion: Positive drilling results reinforce resource potential; focus on imminent MRE updates and Scoping Study. No material financial or structural changes noted.

Material Information Summary

Exploration Results (Key Points for Trading/Capital Markets Impact)

  • Babbler Gold Prospect (7km SSE of Bluebird):
  • Large-scale gold anomaly identified via historical drilling, with significant intercepts:
    • 13m @ 0.48 g/t Au (incl. 7m @ 0.68 g/t Au)
    • 22m @ 0.42 g/t Au (incl. 3m @ 2.91 g/t Au)
    • Anomalous copper in drillholes (e.g., 56m @ 251ppm Cu).

  • Potential for kilometre-scale gold system; untested since 1970s.

  • Wedge Copper-Gold Prospect (5km SW of Bluebird):

  • Fault-bound zone with ironstone/gossan; soil samples show Cu/Fe/Bi anomalies.

  • Rock chip samples up to 150ppm Cu, 112ppm Bi, 6ppm Ag.

  • Next Steps:

  • Wide-spaced RC drilling planned to test both targets.
  • Continued collaboration on regional shared copper-gold processing facility (scoping study underway).

No Capital Raisings, Financials, or Timetable Disclosed

  • Announcement is exploration-focused; no material financial or corporate actions noted.

Conclusion: Positive exploration update highlighting potential resource expansion, but no immediate trading catalysts (e.g., financing, production timelines). Focus on drilling results and target scale.

Material Information Summary:

  • Substantial Holding Disclosure: BGH Capital and its associated entities (via SPV 5382917 Limited) have acquired a 17.795% stake in Tourism Holdings Limited (THL) (NZX: THL), totaling 39,345,432 shares.
  • Breakdown of Holdings:

  • 13,265,883 shares (6.000%) acquired via on-market purchases from ANZ (8,843,922 shares at NZ$2.30/share) and ACC (4,421,961 shares at NZ$2.25/share), settling 18 June 2025.

  • If SPV/BGH acquires full control (via scheme/takeover) within 12 months at a higher price, sellers receive the difference vs. agreed sale prices.
  • Matching payments triggered if SPV buys additional shares at prices >5c above acquisition prices within 20 business days.
  • Strategic Intent: BGH/Trouchet collaboration to explore takeover or scheme of arrangement for THL, with exclusivity until 14 Dec 2025.

Key Impact: Potential catalyst for THL’s valuation due to strategic stake accumulation and looming control transaction. Pricing mechanisms suggest upside if higher bid emerges.
